Although I'm not a long-distance runner, what I find empowering about running is that you can easily change your immediate surroundings and mindset. As a result, you begin to feel a sense of freedom and confidence with each stride you take. 

I love to find products that accompany this feeling, like @athleta summer training capsule. I've been competitively running in their pieces for some time now and still love how my body moves while wearing them. If you want to run, don't worry about how you look, how far you run, or how much you sweat. Start with finding something comfortable to run in; it's always tights for me. Then set small milestones. Start to switch between walking and running, even if it's 15 minutes! You'll be surprised how less scary it is when you break it down.

Happy #nationalrunningday to everyone at every level.

Over a year into the post-competition journey and still figuring out all the things.🙃 Dropping my truths to help anyone else dealing with their own big changes. Add to my list👇🏾
 * change is hard
 * external validation doesn’t determine your worth
 * grieving is part of the process
 * your identity is not what you do
 * time and space are healing
 * some people are only in your life for a season
 * there is joy in starting new things
 * your best can still be in front of you
 * give yourself grace
